If I can't escape, I'd rather die.

272
00:30:19,260 --> 00:30:20,560
Don't do anything crazy.

273
00:30:20,970 --> 00:30:24,530
It's easy to die. Living is what's hard.

274
00:30:26,570 --> 00:30:29,500
Just think of your parents.

275
00:30:29,700 --> 00:30:31,040
You owe it to them...

276
00:30:31,230 --> 00:30:32,800
to keep on living.

277
00:30:35,170 --> 00:30:37,770
Wait until you can go about more freely.

278
00:30:37,980 --> 00:30:39,450
Then think of a way to run away.

279
00:30:40,140 --> 00:30:41,300
Chen, want a drink?

280
00:30:41,640 --> 00:30:42,760
No thanks.

281
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:45,500
We have to go. Come see us soon.

282
00:30:45,780 --> 00:30:46,130
Take care.

283
00:30:46,330 --> 00:30:47,280
Okay.

284
00:30:47,870 --> 00:30:49,160
Come and see me.

285
00:33:43,980 --> 00:33:45,450
Why'd you buy two piglets?

286
00:33:46,070 --> 00:33:48,710
Why not? We have to pay the tax anyway.

287
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:49,770
Where'd you get the money?

288
00:33:49,970 --> 00:33:51,050
Borrowed it.

289
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:53,580
You always borrow money.
See if you can pay it back!

290
00:33:54,880 --> 00:33:55,980
Women don't understand shit.

291
00:34:01,340 --> 00:34:02,110
Fourth Uncle.

292
00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:02,900
You've come. Come in.

293
00:34:03,220 --> 00:34:04,090
Did you buy these piglets?

294
00:34:04,300 --> 00:34:05,150
Borrowed them.

295
00:34:07,740 --> 00:34:08,410
Where's my cousin?

296
00:34:08,620 --> 00:34:09,630
In the field.

297
00:34:15,230 --> 00:34:16,860
Cousin, are you feeling better?

298
00:34:17,170 --> 00:34:18,390
I'm not your cousin!

299
00:34:19,430 --> 00:34:22,470
Sorry. I'm your husband's cousin.
My name is Decheng.

300
00:34:22,710 --> 00:34:24,410
My name means "integrity."

301
00:34:25,420 --> 00:34:28,450
You're that teacher.
Thanks for saving my life.

302
00:34:29,530 --> 00:34:32,560
I didn't do anything.
I've wanted to stop by.

303
00:34:34,190 --> 00:34:36,970
Teacher Huang,
just call me by my first name.

304
00:34:37,180 --> 00:34:38,850
I shouldn't. Don't call me 'teacher.'

305
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:40,560
You were in school longer than me.

306
00:34:43,720 --> 00:34:46,230
I brought you a few books.
I hope you'll like them..

307
00:34:46,810 --> 00:34:48,000
I don't have any good books.

308
00:34:53,670 --> 00:34:54,960
Uncle, see you!

309
00:35:22,550 --> 00:35:25,920
You just read these stupid books!
Feed the pigs!

310
00:35:48,570 --> 00:35:50,000
Are you trying to burn the pigs?

311
00:35:50,940 --> 00:35:54,070
If anything happens to them,
I'll beat you to death!

312
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:44,410
Village Chief! Village Chief!

313
00:36:46,460 --> 00:36:47,270
Village Chief!

314
00:36:47,610 --> 00:36:48,450
What is it?

315
00:36:48,800 --> 00:36:49,740
She wants to see you.

316
00:36:50,470 --> 00:36:54,260
Oh, your case.
I'm still looking into it.

317
00:36:54,710 --> 00:36:56,560
I still haven't heard back
from the police.

318
00:36:57,080 --> 00:36:59,240
Go on back.

319
00:36:59,970 --> 00:37:02,510
I'll let you know when I hear something.

320
00:37:04,350 --> 00:37:05,120
Thank you.

321
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:05,880
No problem.

322
00:37:06,090 --> 00:37:06,680
Get back to your game.

323
00:37:06,890 --> 00:37:08,630
Take care.

324
00:37:09,920 --> 00:37:10,960
Snake eyes!

325
00:37:13,290 --> 00:37:14,130
Royal flush!

326
00:37:56,680 --> 00:37:58,730
Chen, I can't take it.

327
00:37:58,930 --> 00:38:00,370
Which road should I take to run away?

328
00:38:01,090 --> 00:38:03,870
Don't take the big road.
Take the small path out.

329
00:38:04,160 --> 00:38:05,750
Once over the mountain,
you'll see the main road.

330
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:07,220
Then you'll have made it.

331
00:38:07,810 --> 00:38:08,950
Which mountain?

332
00:38:10,900 --> 00:38:12,020
The tallest mountain over there.

333
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:35,060
Auntie, what are you singing?

334
00:38:36,790 --> 00:38:37,630
Do you like it?

335
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:38,740
Yes.

336
00:38:42,530 --> 00:38:43,570
What's your name?

337
00:38:43,780 --> 00:38:44,770
Li Qingshan.

338
00:38:44,970 --> 00:38:45,950
Are you in school?

339
00:38:46,290 --> 00:38:47,130
Yes.

340
00:38:47,330 --> 00:38:47,920
Which grade?

341
00:38:48,130 --> 00:38:49,120
Fourth.

342
00:38:49,350 --> 00:38:51,470
Don't call me Auntie.

343
00:38:51,680 --> 00:38:53,010
Call me Sister Bai, okay?

344
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:54,150
Okay.

345
00:38:54,430 --> 00:38:55,370
Go on. Say it.

346
00:38:55,570 --> 00:38:56,590
Sister Bai.

347
00:39:06,190 --> 00:39:07,270
You're here.

348
00:39:08,270 --> 00:39:10,010
So this is your college-educated wife.

349
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:13,390
You owe me a drink.

350
00:39:13,600 --> 00:39:14,850
Then come over for a drink.

351
00:39:15,060 --> 00:39:16,010
Next time.

352
00:39:17,500 --> 00:39:18,850
- See you.
- Take care.

353
00:39:34,510 --> 00:39:37,110
She's listening to you now, right?
I told you she just needed a beating.

354
00:39:38,230 --> 00:39:40,710
It's 1 5.80.

355
00:39:40,910 --> 00:39:41,990
Put it on my tab.

356
00:39:43,450 --> 00:39:44,880
Come and get this.

357
00:39:48,710 --> 00:39:51,420
Come if you need anything.

358
00:39:54,730 --> 00:39:55,280
What do you want?

359
00:39:55,490 --> 00:39:56,470
A bag of salt.

360
00:40:02,660 --> 00:40:05,370
See that woman? She tried to run away.

361
00:40:06,070 --> 00:40:08,880
Same thing would happen to you.

362
00:40:43,570 --> 00:40:45,200
Chen, I'm going to run away.

363
00:40:45,410 --> 00:40:46,450
Be careful.

364
00:40:46,660 --> 00:40:48,520
If you make it, tell my folks I'm here.

365
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:49,530
Ask them to come save me.

366
00:40:49,730 --> 00:40:50,630
Okay.

367
00:40:59,150 --> 00:40:59,890
Where are you going?

368
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:01,070
To pee.

369
00:41:36,140 --> 00:41:38,030
Have you seen Xue Mei?

370
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:40,910
Not good for much,
but sure knows how to pee.

371
00:41:42,610 --> 00:41:45,220
Your clothes got washed away.

372
00:42:11,220 --> 00:42:13,930
You two follow the road.
Er Hu, follow me.

373
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:27,400
Excuse me, which way into town?

374
00:42:28,090 --> 00:42:29,030
Thanks.

375
00:42:35,460 --> 00:42:36,600
Have you seen a woman run by?

376
00:43:14,780 --> 00:43:15,930
- Have you see her?
- No.

377
00:43:16,140 --> 00:43:17,280
To the town.

378
00:43:45,630 --> 00:43:46,850
Hi, can you give me a ride?

379
00:43:47,090 --> 00:43:48,560
- Where to?
- lnto town.

380
00:43:48,770 --> 00:43:50,720
- Three bucks.
- I don't have any money.

381
00:43:50,920 --> 00:43:53,150
Then forget it.
I usually charge five bucks.

382
00:43:53,360 --> 00:43:54,800
Please help me. I don't have any money.

383
00:43:55,000 --> 00:43:58,370
No way. If everyone wanted a free ride,
I'd be broke.

384
00:43:58,580 --> 00:43:59,660
Help me.

385
00:44:32,710 --> 00:44:33,860
You thought you could run away!

386
00:44:34,170 --> 00:44:35,080
Let me go.

387
00:45:05,450 --> 00:45:06,630
Come back.

388
00:45:06,840 --> 00:45:07,570
You still run away?

389
00:45:07,960 --> 00:45:10,810
I give you stuff to eat
and buy you new clothes.

390
00:45:11,010 --> 00:45:11,890
What else do you want?

391
00:45:12,090 --> 00:45:14,430
- Stop beating her. You'll kill her.
- Stay out of it.

392
00:45:14,630 --> 00:45:17,040
Bitch, I can make you obey me if I want.

393
00:45:54,130 --> 00:45:56,460
Sister Bai, here you are.
It's still warm.

394
00:45:57,600 --> 00:45:58,710
No, thanks.

395
00:45:59,030 --> 00:46:00,010
Take it.

396
00:46:04,730 --> 00:46:05,770
Thank you.

397
00:46:28,570 --> 00:46:29,470
Fourth Aunt.

398
00:46:30,550 --> 00:46:31,390
You're here.

399
00:46:39,700 --> 00:46:42,310
I wanted to come earlier,
but I've been too busy.

400
00:46:43,180 --> 00:46:46,900
Are you better?
I borrowed some more books for you.

401
00:46:48,040 --> 00:46:48,890
Thanks.

402
00:46:51,140 --> 00:46:54,310
The people here aren't well educated.
They're barbaric.

403
00:46:54,730 --> 00:46:57,030
I'm the only one
who went to high school.

404
00:46:57,750 --> 00:46:59,460
I always dreamed of going to college.

405
00:47:00,330 --> 00:47:01,620
I wanted to leave this mountain village.

406
00:47:02,660 --> 00:47:04,480
I never did well on the entrance exam.

407
00:47:04,930 --> 00:47:06,180
I could only come back to teach.

408
00:47:06,770 --> 00:47:08,720
Isn't it good being a teacher?

409
00:47:09,170 --> 00:47:10,120
Sure.

410
00:47:10,730 --> 00:47:13,930
But the pay is low,
and we don't get paid on time.

411
00:47:15,260 --> 00:47:18,040
I've had it. I feel like quitting.

412
00:47:21,140 --> 00:47:22,910
Don't laugh at me.

413
00:47:23,430 --> 00:47:26,990
I'm a teacher
but haven't even seen a train.

414
00:47:27,570 --> 00:47:29,240
I've seen a train.

415
00:47:29,660 --> 00:47:32,660
Look what happened?
I was still kidnapped.

416
00:47:35,610 --> 00:47:37,700
How could you have believed those guys?

417
00:47:38,920 --> 00:47:40,450
I really don't know.

418
00:47:40,960 --> 00:47:42,430
I had just graduated

419
00:47:42,640 --> 00:47:44,590
and couldn't find a good job.

420
00:47:44,800 --> 00:47:46,880
My folks owed lots of people money.

421
00:47:47,200 --> 00:47:48,970
My brother also needed tuition.

422
00:47:49,460 --> 00:47:52,140
I wanted to help
my folks pay back the money.

423
00:47:52,410 --> 00:47:54,500
And help my brother pay tuition.

424
00:47:55,890 --> 00:47:59,690
They said I'd make lots of money
by selling medicine.

425
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:01,520
So I came here with them.

426
00:48:02,370 --> 00:48:05,110
After I came here,
I drank a cup of water.

427
00:48:06,720 --> 00:48:08,420
Then I don't remember what happened.

428
00:48:12,380 --> 00:48:13,740
Tell me,

429
00:48:14,120 --> 00:48:17,570
What was it like to live
on a college campus?

430
00:48:18,090 --> 00:48:19,310
Nothing special.

431
00:48:22,710 --> 00:48:25,120
What a waste marrying him.

432
00:48:25,390 --> 00:48:26,550
I didn't marry him.

433
00:48:28,980 --> 00:48:32,500
Decheng, can you help me?

434
00:48:33,790 --> 00:48:40,960
I do feel great sympathy for you.
I do want to help you.

435
00:48:42,340 --> 00:48:45,410
Really? Then can you help me to escape?

436
00:48:45,920 --> 00:48:51,980
That's hard.
You do know that he's my cousin?

437
00:48:52,190 --> 00:48:53,130
De Cheng, you're here.

438
00:48:53,680 --> 00:48:55,760
Uncle. Cousin.

439
00:48:57,090 --> 00:48:58,830
- Cousin, hi.
- What are you doing?

440
00:48:59,040 --> 00:49:01,060
Nothing. I brought some books.

441
00:49:01,410 --> 00:49:03,040
So she's not bored all day.

442
00:49:03,360 --> 00:49:07,080
She does nothing but read.

443
00:49:07,290 --> 00:49:08,360
You're still not satisfied?

444
00:49:12,080 --> 00:49:13,790
She's just a fucking waste of my money.

445
00:49:14,520 --> 00:49:18,320
It's going to take a while
to pay you back.

446
00:49:18,560 --> 00:49:20,150
No problem. There's no hurry.

447
00:49:37,170 --> 00:49:40,550
Mailman!

448
00:49:44,480 --> 00:49:46,990
Can you mail this for me?

449
00:49:47,190 --> 00:49:49,870
I don't have any stamps,
but I'll pay you later.

450
00:49:58,910 --> 00:49:59,900
Thanks.

451
00:52:57,150 --> 00:52:59,760
Chen, why haven't you come by to see me?

452
00:53:00,150 --> 00:53:01,330
I'm bored out of my mind.

453
00:53:01,580 --> 00:53:03,170
We were just thinking
of going to see you.

454
00:53:05,640 --> 00:53:06,480
How's it going with her?

455
00:53:07,210 --> 00:53:10,340
Nothing new. She can do some work.

456
00:53:10,970 --> 00:53:12,190
Is her tummy getting larger yet?

457
00:53:12,530 --> 00:53:13,230
No.

458
00:53:13,440 --> 00:53:16,220
Why not? It's been months
and she's still not pregnant.

459
00:53:16,500 --> 00:53:19,170
Who knows. We're worried sick.

460
00:53:19,490 --> 00:53:21,450
Just make your son take some medicine.

461
00:53:21,650 --> 00:53:22,940
Make him work extra hard at night.

462
00:53:26,410 --> 00:53:28,570
Can you lend me some money?

463
00:53:29,130 --> 00:53:30,240
I've been here years

464
00:53:30,450 --> 00:53:31,710
and have never seen a cent.

465
00:53:32,190 --> 00:53:33,030
When I have money,

466
00:53:33,230 --> 00:53:34,870
I'll pay you back double.

467
00:53:35,320 --> 00:53:37,070
They always pay for things.

468
00:53:37,270 --> 00:53:38,830
They're afraid
I'll run away with their money.

469
00:53:40,510 --> 00:53:43,110
Can you go to the police station
and make a report?

470
00:53:43,530 --> 00:53:44,570
It's not so simple.

471
00:53:44,790 --> 00:53:46,520
They side with the locals.

472
00:53:47,180 --> 00:53:48,220
When Gui Hua filed a report,

473
00:53:48,430 --> 00:53:51,020
the police didn't care.
They said it was a family dispute.

474
00:53:51,220 --> 00:53:53,340
Her husband beat her until
he broke her leg.

475
00:53:53,790 --> 00:53:55,950
None of us have succeeded at running away.

476
00:53:56,440 --> 00:53:57,690
It's best to accept our fate.

477
00:53:58,080 --> 00:53:59,330
I no longer want to escape.

478
00:53:59,750 --> 00:54:01,250
I've got two kids.

479
00:54:01,550 --> 00:54:03,020
What if I did get out?

480
00:54:03,290 --> 00:54:04,330
What about the kids?

481
00:54:05,320 --> 00:54:06,710
What man would still want me?

482
00:54:07,680 --> 00:54:09,080
Life can be so hard.

483
00:54:11,650 --> 00:54:13,730
It's best not to think too much.

484
00:54:13,940 --> 00:54:15,300
Look after your health first.

485
00:54:31,540 --> 00:54:33,570
Aunt, hello.

486
00:54:34,120 --> 00:54:35,380
I've got some books for my cousin's wife.

487
00:54:36,450 --> 00:54:37,470
She's inside.

488
00:54:40,620 --> 00:54:43,790
Stupid books!

489
00:54:49,700 --> 00:54:51,410
You're here. Come in. Sit down.

490
00:54:52,000 --> 00:54:53,960
I borrowed a few more books for you.

491
00:54:54,570 --> 00:54:55,520
Thanks.

492
00:54:55,790 --> 00:54:56,590
You're welcome.

493
00:55:17,710 --> 00:55:20,790
I just want you to know that
I really do want to help you.

494
00:55:21,720 --> 00:55:24,150
I know. You're different from them.

495
00:55:25,120 --> 00:55:26,450
You're educated.

496
00:55:27,730 --> 00:55:30,730
But you must not rush.

497
00:55:31,080 --> 00:55:32,850
You know what things are like here.

498
00:55:33,200 --> 00:55:34,520
I've got to come up with a good plan.

499
00:55:34,970 --> 00:55:36,890
Stop fighting. Eat your own.

500
00:55:39,730 --> 00:55:41,100
Aunt, I got to go.

501
00:55:47,740 --> 00:55:52,760
Listen up.
This is an important announcement.

502
00:55:53,030 --> 00:55:56,820
Party officials are coming
to inspect the village.

503
00:55:57,580 --> 00:56:02,150
Every home must be cleaned and tidied up.

504
00:56:02,600 --> 00:56:09,300
Respect the leaders. Watch what you say.

505
00:56:09,900 --> 00:56:13,730
Whoever ruins the village's reputation...

506
00:56:13,930 --> 00:56:17,100
will pay a price.

507
00:56:17,590 --> 00:56:19,930
We will not let you off lightly.

508
00:56:20,510 --> 00:56:21,490
Listen again.

509
00:56:21,690 --> 00:56:27,610
Whoever ruins the village's reputation...

510
00:56:27,930 --> 00:56:30,990
will pay a price.

511
00:56:56,770 --> 00:57:14,890
We warmly welcome you!

512
00:57:38,890 --> 00:57:40,880
We're here. Get down.

513
00:57:44,780 --> 00:57:45,860
That's the village council.

514
00:57:49,610 --> 00:57:51,320
After you, please.

515
00:57:55,600 --> 00:57:57,190
The Party officials have left.

516
00:57:58,310 --> 00:58:01,480
Let's go back. We're damn starving!

517
00:58:26,280 --> 00:58:27,850
- Do I have a letter?
- No.

518
00:58:29,830 --> 00:58:31,570
Can you help send another letter for me?

519
00:58:31,780 --> 00:58:32,800
Okay.

520
00:58:33,420 --> 00:58:34,890
Thanks.

521
00:58:35,090 --> 00:58:36,030
You're welcome.

522
00:58:53,070 --> 00:58:53,770
De Gui.

523
00:58:54,190 --> 00:58:54,990
What is it?

524
00:58:55,620 --> 00:58:57,910
The school would like
your wife to help out. Okay?

525
00:58:58,120 --> 00:58:58,990
Just for a bit.

526
00:58:59,790 --> 00:59:00,660
What can she do?

527
00:59:00,980 --> 00:59:02,600
Her education is better than ours.

528
00:59:03,550 --> 00:59:05,840
Then keep an eye on her.
Don't let her run away.

529
00:59:06,120 --> 00:59:08,420
Don't worry.
I'll definitely bring her back.

530
00:59:10,890 --> 00:59:13,080
Hey, come on and help them at school.

531
01:00:03,840 --> 01:00:04,990
Why'd you come get me?

532
01:00:05,820 --> 01:00:06,940
We only have two teachers.

533
01:00:07,150 --> 01:00:08,810
One just went home.

534
01:00:09,440 --> 01:00:10,390
Some tea?

535
01:00:13,130 --> 01:00:13,960
I'm not thirsty.

536
01:00:19,820 --> 01:00:22,080
Actually the school doesn't need you.

537
01:00:22,800 --> 01:00:25,970
This is the only place

538
01:00:26,250 --> 01:00:28,130
we can really talk.

539
01:00:29,760 --> 01:00:32,270
Can you help me get out of here?

540
01:00:32,470 --> 01:00:33,940
I will. I promise.

541
01:00:34,140 --> 01:00:35,260
I'll help you leave this place.

542
01:00:36,090 --> 01:00:37,130
Don't lie to me.

543
01:00:37,340 --> 01:00:38,320
I would never lie to you.

544
01:01:10,530 --> 01:01:11,270
